       np->rxopt.bits.rxinfo || np->rxopt.bits.rxoinfo ||
       np->rxopt.bits.rxhlim || np->rxopt.bits.rxohlim) {
       atomic_inc(&skb->users);
       ireq->pktopts = skb;
   }
   ```
   The code copies relevant fields from the parsed options (`tcp_opt`) and the packet (`skb`) into the new request socket (`req`). If additional options are accepted, it increments the reference count of the `skb` and assigns it to `ireq->pktopts`. This ensures that the `skb` remains valid as long as the request socket is in use.

3. **Initializing New Socket Options**:
   ```c
   ireq->snd_wscale    = tcp_opt.snd_wscale;
   ireq->sack_ok       = tcp_opt.sack_ok;
   ireq->wscale_ok     = tcp_opt.wscale_ok;
   ireq->tstamp_ok     = tcp_opt.saw_tstamp;
