   treq->snt_synack.v64= 0;
   treq->rcv_isn = ntohl(th->seq) - 1;
   treq->snt_isn = cookie;
   ```
   The code initializes the new socket's options using the values from `tcp_opt`, ensuring that the new socket has its own set of options independent of the original socket.

### Conclusion:
The code snippet demonstrates behavior that aligns with the solution behavior described in the vulnerability knowledge. It safely accesses and copies socket options from the incoming packet and initializes the new socket's options independently, thus preventing potential use-after-free scenarios.

